Voting Application
Overview
The Voting Application is a backend system designed to facilitate a secure and efficient voting process. It provides features for user authentication, candidate management, and voting functionalities. This application ensures a streamlined voting experience with robust admin controls and secure user interactions.

Features
User Authentication: Sign up and log in using Aadhar Card Number and password.
Voting: Users can view a list of candidates and cast a vote (one-time only).
Candidate Management: Admins can add, update, and delete candidates.
Admin Restrictions: Admins are restricted from voting.
User Profile Management: Users can view their profile and change their password.
Technologies Used
Node.js: JavaScript runtime for building scalable network applications.
Express.js: Web framework for building APIs.
MongoDB: NoSQL database for storing user and candidate information.
JSON Web Tokens (JWT): For secure authentication and authorization.
